subSubSection.paragraph:
Thorax.
The outer stripes of the head continued to the middle area of metazona, between them with a brown stripe (
Figure 6A
); anterior margin of pronotum slightly projecting, posterior margin narrowly rounded; the lateral lobe longer than high (
Figure 6B
).

Abdomen.
Dorsal margin of tergites and sternites black, lateral margin of abdominal tergites yellowish. Tenth abdominal tergite with arch-shaped concavity; epiproct tongue-shaped. 
Cerci.
Yellow. Basal half with keel-shaped dorsal lobe, ventral process longer, which curved dorsad, apices obtuse (
Figure 6C, D
). Apical half of cerci spineshaped, squarely incurved, apices subacute (
Figure 6E, H
). Subgenital plate with base broad, gradually narrowing, basal margin slightly straight, with 1 V-shaped membranous area; apical area nearly rectangular projected in middle, centre of posterior margin slightly concave, the lateral lobe obtusely rounded (
Figure 6G
). Styli conical, apices obtuse, inserted on the subapex of subgenital plate.
